    "body": "Hey @Skyge, the method seems to be `_signTypedData` according to the [docs](https://docs.ethers.io/v5/single-page/#/v5/api/signer/-%23-Signer-signTypedData)\r\n\r\nThat being said, we don't expose that method in our wrapped signer. I'm not sure if we should do it or if we should wait until that method is stable.\r\n\r\nAs a workaround, you can access the underlying signer with `._signer`, so this should work:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nconst signature = await owner._signer._signTypedData(domain, types, value);\r\n```",
